  "prompt": "Which country invented the sandwich?",
  "response": "The sandwich is widely believed to have been popularized in England during the 18th century. The story often attributed to its invention is that John Montagu, the 4th Earl of Sandwich, requested his meat to be served between two slices of bread so that he could eat while continuing to play card games without getting his hands greasy. This made it convenient to eat without utensils, and the concept quickly gained popularity, leading to the creation of the term \"sandwich.\" While similar forms of food existed in various cultures before this, the modern sandwich as we know it is generally credited to England.",
